The "bird flu" has claimed four victims in Hong Kong, with two deaths reported, including a 54-year-old man.
Health officials are monitoring seven staff members with flu-like symptoms.
Hospitals are testing all patients for the flu, including relatives of infected individuals.
Imported poultry is deemed safe, with strict examinations conducted before entering the market.
Experts in Macao advise caution but urge residents not to panic.
There is no evidence of human-to-human transmission, and authorities are closely monitoring chicken diseases in neighboring provinces.
Precautionary measures include avoiding contact with birds and maintaining good hygiene practices.
